!! !!Normative/prescriptive compounding tags
!! (to govern compound behaviour for the speller, ie what a compound SHOULD BE)

                !! !The first part of the component may be ...
+CmpN/Sg        !!≈ | @CODE@ | Sg
+CmpN/SgN       !!≈ | @CODE@ | SgNominative
+CmpN/SgG       !!≈ | @CODE@ | SgGenitive
+CmpN/PlG       !!≈ | @CODE@ | PlGenitive

                !! !This part of the component might be ...
+CmpN/First     !!≈ | @CODE@ | first
+CmpN/Last      !!≈ | @CODE@ | last
+CmpN/None      !!≈ | @CODE@ | Can not take part in compounds
+CmpN/Only      !!≈ | @CODE@ | Can only be part of a compound
+CmpN/Pref      !!≈ | @CODE@ | prefix only

                !! !The second part of the compound may take ...
+CmpN/SgLeft    !!≈ | @CODE@ | Sg to the left
+CmpN/SgNomLeft !!≈ | @CODE@ | etc.
+CmpN/SgGenLeft !!≈ | @CODE@ | "
+CmpN/PlGenLeft !!≈ | @CODE@ | "

                !! !This part of the compound may ... 
+CmpN/All       !!≈ | @CODE@ | all positions, __default__, this tag does not have to be written
+CmpN/Def       !!≈ | @CODE@ | works along with Left compound-tagging
+CmpN/DefSgGen  !!≈ | @CODE@ | works along with Left compound-tagging
+CmpN/DefPlGen  !!≈ | @CODE@ | works along with Left compound-tagging

!! !!Descriptive compounding tags
!! Tags for compound analysis - this is what a compound actually is:

  +SgCmp +SgNomCmp +SgGenCmp +PlGenCmp !!≈ ; @CODE@ : Different case + number combinations
  +Cmp     !!≈ ; @CODE@ : Dynamic compound - this tag should ''always'' be part of a dynamic compound.
           !!  It is important for Apertium, and useful in other cases as well.
  +RCmpnd  !!≈ ; @CODE@ : This is a split compound with the other part to the right: \\
           !!  "Arbeids- og inkluderingsdepartementet" => Arbeids- = +RCmpnd
  +LCmpnd+ !!≈ ; @CODE@ : This is a split compound with the other part to the left
  +ShCmp   !!≈ ; @CODE@ : Testing ShCmp

